.TH "do_fw_call_hvc" 9 "do_fw_call_hvc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
do_fw_call_hvc \- Call system-level platform management layer (HVC)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" do_fw_call_hvc
.BI "(u64 arg0 "  ","
.BI "u64 arg1 "  ","
.BI "u64 arg2 "  ","
.BI "u32 *ret_payload "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "arg0" 12
Argument 0 to HVC call
.IP "arg1" 12
Argument 1 to HVC call
.IP "arg2" 12
Argument 2 to HVC call
.IP "ret_payload" 12
Returned value array
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Invoke platform management function via HVC
HVC-based for communication through hypervisor
(no direct communication with ATF).
.SH "RETURN"
Returns status, either success or error+reason
